</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus spirator" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spirator">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus spirator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Townes, 1971.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
It is a small Neotropical genus with five species; one Afrotropical species with large propodeal spiracles described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Khalaim, AI" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="101 - 110" refId="B5" refString="Khalaim, AI, 2007. First records of Meggoleus, Heterocola and Phradis (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Tersilochinae) from the Afrotropical region, with description of four new species. African Invertebrates 48 (2): 101 - 110" title="First records of Meggoleus, Heterocola and Phradis (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Tersilochinae) from the Afrotropical region, with description of four new species." volume="48" year="2007">Khalaim 2007</bibRefCitation>
) was recently found to belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Allophrys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allophrys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Allophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="FÃ¶rster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Khalaim, AI" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="365 - 370" refId="B7" refString="Khalaim, AI, 2017. A new species of Allophrys Foerster, 1869 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Tersilochinae) with large propodeal spiracles from Indonesia. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS 321 (4): 365 - 370" title="A new species of Allophrys Foerster, 1869 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Tersilochinae) with large propodeal spiracles from Indonesia." volume="321" year="2017">Khalaim 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Nothing is known about host range of any 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in South America were revised by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.163.2291" author="Alvarado, M" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="83 - 90" refId="B1" refString="Alvarado, M, 2012. Discovery of the genus Meggoleus Townes, 1971 (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Tersilochinae) in Peru, with the description of two new species. ZooKeys 163: 83 - 90, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.163.2291" title="Discovery of the genus Meggoleus Townes, 1971 (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Tersilochinae) in Peru, with the description of two new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.163.2291" volume="163" year="2012">Alvarado (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Two of them, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. spirator" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spirator">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. spirator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Townes and 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pampahermosensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="pampahermosensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. pampahermosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Alvarado, are known from Costa Rica (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3185.1.2" author="Khalaim, AI" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="36 - 52" refId="B10" refString="Khalaim, AI, Broad, GR, 2012. Tersilochinae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) of Costa Rica, part 1. Genera Allophrys Foerster, Barycnemis Foerster and Meggoleus Townes. Zootaxa 3185: 36 - 52, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3185.1.2" title="Tersilochinae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) of Costa Rica, part 1. Genera Allophrys Foerster, Barycnemis Foerster and Meggoleus Townes." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3185.1.2" volume="3185" year="2012">Khalaim and Broad 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4486.1.1" author="Khalaim, AI" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 30" refId="B18" refString="Khalaim, AI, Kasparyan, DR, Lopez-Ortega, M, 2018. New records and descriptions of Ichneumonidae (Hymenoptera) from Mexico. Zootaxa 4486 (1): 1 - 30, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4486.1.1" title="New records and descriptions of Ichneumonidae (Hymenoptera) from Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4486.1.1" volume="4486" year="2018">Khalaim et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), and the latter species was recorded also from Mexico (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4486.1.1" author="Khalaim, AI" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 30" refId="B18" refString="Khalaim, AI, Kasparyan, DR, Lopez-Ortega, M, 2018. New records and descriptions of Ichneumonidae (Hymenoptera) from Mexico. Zootaxa 4486 (1): 1 - 30, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4486.1.1" title="New records and descriptions of Ichneumonidae (Hymenoptera) from Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4486.1.1" volume="4486" year="2018">Khalaim et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In this paper, we describe two new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Mexico and Panama. Both new species possess small propodeal spiracles, clearly differing from three previously known taxa which are characterized by strongly enlarged propodeal spiracles. Record of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. hidalgoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hidalgoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. hidalgoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. from Tamaulipas is a northernmost known locality for the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A partial key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Meggoleus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meggoleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Meggoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with small propodeal spiracles is provided.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
